
Overview of noun chorus

The noun chorus has 5 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (3) chorus -- (any utterance produced simultaneously by a group; "a chorus of boos")
2. (1) chorus -- (a group of people assembled to sing together)
3. (1) refrain, chorus -- (the part of a song where a soloist is joined by a group of singers)
4. chorus, chorus line -- (a body of dancers or singers who perform together)
5. chorus, Greek chorus -- (a company of actors who comment (by speaking or singing in unison) on the action in a classical Greek play)

Overview of verb chorus

The verb chorus has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (1) chorus -- (utter in unison; "`yes,' the children chorused")
2. choir, chorus -- (sing in a choir)
